## Exact logic changes

### 1) API Gateway multipart forwarding fix
File: `backend/api-gateway/src/routes/proxyRoutes.ts`
- Fixed multipart proxy header forwarding so uploads reach Multer correctly.
- Key fixes:
  - Forward `content-type` (including multipart boundary).
  - Forward `content-length` when present.
  - Forward `accept` and `transfer-encoding` when present.
  - Use normalized lowercase header keys (`authorization`, `content-type`).
- Why: without boundary/header forwarding, media files can be dropped and posts become text-only/empty.

### 2) Feed createPost validation hardening
File: `backend/feed-service/src/controllers/postController.ts`
- Added server-side guard:
  - Reject post if it has no text, no media, and no poll options.
- Why: prevents silent creation of blank posts if upload parsing fails upstream.

### 3) Feed upload validator support expanded
File: `backend/feed-service/src/middleware/uploadValidator.ts`
- Added `video/ogg` signature support (`OggS` magic bytes).
- Added `video/ogg` to allowed MIME list and error messaging.
- Why: frontend allows OGG; backend previously rejected it.

### 4) Feed post type inference fixed for OGG
File: `backend/feed-service/src/services/postService.ts`
- Updated media type inference regex from `(mp4|webm)` to `(mp4|webm|ogg)`.
- Why: OGG uploads were being misclassified as images when `type=text`.

### 5) Mobile multipart field-name fix
File: `mobile/src/services/feedService.ts`
- Changed media append key from `media[0]`, `media[1]`, ... to repeated `media`.
- Removed manual `'Content-Type': 'multipart/form-data'` override.
- Added `type` form field (`video` if any selected media is video; else `image`).
- Why: backend expects `memoryUpload.array('media', 5)` and boundary should be auto-managed.

### 6) start.bat rewritten
File: `start.bat`
- Replaced script with a Docker-first startup flow.
- Added infra container start (`decp-postgres`, `decp-redis`, `decp-rabbitmq`).
- Added PostgreSQL readiness wait and DB auto-create loop.
- Added upload directory checks.
- Added dependency install checks and backend build step.
- Added service launch with environment variables (DB host/port/user/password + internal token).
- Added gateway wait + seed execution + final URLs.

IMPORTANT:
- This rewritten script currently hardcodes DB port `5433` for services.
- During my local checks, this machine had PostgreSQL listening on `5432`, not `5433`.
- Another AI should make this auto-detect/fallback (`5433` then `5432`) to avoid startup failures.

### 7) reset-db.js updated for current config inputs
File: `reset-db.js`
- DB connection now reads env vars with defaults:
  - `DB_HOST` (default `localhost`)
  - `DB_PORT` (default `5433`)
  - `DB_USER` (default `postgres`)
  - `DB_PASSWORD` (default `12345`)
- Improved startup log to print host/port.

### 8) seed.js modernized + media seed path
File: `seed.js`
- Added API host/port env support:
  - `API_HOST` (default `localhost`)
  - `API_PORT` (default `3000`)
- Added helper utilities:
  - `extractPostId()`
  - multipart capability check (`fetch/FormData/Blob`)
  - seed image/video path resolution (`SEED_IMAGE_FILE`, `SEED_VIDEO_FILE`)
  - mime-type inference by extension
  - multipart media-post creator against `/api/v1/posts`
- Added media seed behavior in Step 3:
  - Always attempts one image media post via multipart.
  - Attempts one video media post if sample video exists.
  - Logs warning if video sample missing.
- Updated summary line to include media post count.

